# Test Run Schema Rule

## Purpose
This rule defines the convention for running only tests in a specific test suite or class using the project's test runner script.

## Command Schema
To run only the tests in a specific test suite (class) within a test target, use the following command:

```
./run_tests.sh <TestTarget>/<TestSuite>
```

- `<TestTarget>`: The name of the test target (e.g., `magical-storiesUITests`)
- `<TestSuite>`: The name of the test suite/class (e.g., `CollectionDetailUITests`)

## Example
To run only the tests in the `CollectionDetailUITests` suite within the `magical-storiesUITests` target:

```
./run_tests.sh magical-storiesUITests/CollectionDetailUITests
```

This will execute only the tests in the specified suite, leveraging the `-only-testing` flag in [run_tests.sh](mdc:run_tests.sh).

